.el .ds Aq '
.TH pif-config-versions-remove 1  "pif-config-versions-remove " 
.SH NAME
pif\-config\-versions\-remove \- Remove one or more version specs for a system
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBpif\-config\-versions\-remove\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fISYSTEM\fR> <\fIVERSION\fR> 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Remove one or more version specs for a system
.PP
The remaining version specs for SYSTEM are unchanged.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
<\fISYSTEM\fR>
IF system name (e.g. inform, tads3)
.TP
<\fIVERSION\fR>
Version prefix strings to match (e.g. i10 i11.0)

Each string is matched as a prefix against version entries in the registry. For example, "i10" matches "i10.1" and "i10.2.3" but not "i11.0".
